Chapter 1: The Invisible Start
Finn was tired and deeply frustrated. For two years, he had been a Provisional Hunter in the city’s defense force, the Guild. His power was pathetic: Shimmering Hide—it only made his skin slightly blurry, like heat rising off asphalt, and only if he stood perfectly still.
His mission today was simple: Residue Depletion in Sector Four. This meant waiting for the real Hunters to win and then collecting the leftover monster parts.
The Battlefield
Sector Four was a war zone of rubble. The elite Hunters had just finished a pack of small, powerful creatures called Kinetic Vipers. These monsters were known for their blistering speed.
Finn walked onto the street. The air was thick with static energy. A huge, metallic crash signaled the end of the fight.
He approached a defeated Viper. The creature lay still, its gray, armored body intact. As required, Finn used a specialized tool to open the Viper's chest plate.
The creature’s energy core was exposed. The Guild-mandated retrieval target—the primary Kinetic Shard—was a pulsing blue crystal. Finn carefully scooped it up into his official containment pouch.
But deep inside the monster's shattered core, Finn noticed a smaller, jagged fragment. It was a secondary, perfect Silver Shard, humming with rapid energy.
This secondary Shard felt dangerous, exciting. The Guild strictly forbade touching unsanctioned fragments. Finn checked the perimeter. No Hunters nearby, only the distant sound of fighting.
The First Secret
Driven by ambition, Finn quickly slipped the small Silver Shard into his palm.
He felt a sudden, powerful jolt run through his body. The silver crystal didn't just feel fast; it felt like a compressed storm. It dissolved instantly, sinking into his hand.
Finn gasped, biting his lip to suppress the sound. The crystal was gone.
A sudden, aggressive, restless instinct flooded his mind: Move. Run. Never stop. Finn fought the urge to bolt, forcing his mind to focus on the quiet street.
He tried to use his old power—Shimmering Hide—useless.
Then, he focused on the new feeling—the silver energy. He focused it on his legs, testing it cautiously.
He felt an explosive, contained power in his muscles. He took one step, and that single step blurred. He stopped immediately, realizing he had crossed five feet in an instant. He had gained Super Speed.
The Report
Finn wiped the sweat from his brow and quickly finished the cleanup. He ensured no trace of his reckless action remained.
He returned to the Guild Compound. His boss, Commander Silas, a massive man with a serious face and the power of an Invisible Wall, was waiting in his office.
"Report, Provisional Finn," Silas commanded, not smiling.
Finn placed his containment pouch on the desk. "Residue secure, Commander. Tier One Vipers neutralized. Kinetic Shards accounted for."
Silas scanned the pouch. "Good. The city needs those Shards to power our defense grids."
Silas looked at Finn, his eyes searching, perhaps seeing the subtle new tension in Finn's posture. "You seem eager, Finn. Next time, move faster on the retrieval."
Finn nodded, suppressing a smile. I will, he thought. Much, much faster.
He had the Guild's trust and a powerful new secret. His path to strength, hidden and dangerous, had begun.
